President Trump made remarks on healthcare in the East Room of the White House. He expressed his support for families and individuals who have faced difficulties and addiction. The President mentioned Steve Witkoff, a friend and developer, who shared his personal story of losing his son to drug addiction. Trump pledged to take strong action against opioid companies and drug dealers, stating that the administration will be rolling out policies in the next three weeks. He also mentioned the possibility of litigation against opioid companies. The President emphasized the need for strength and toughness in dealing with the drug crisis and suggested that harsh penalties, such as the death penalty, could be effective in reducing drug problems. Trump expressed his support for those affected by addiction and assured them that the administration is fighting for them.